node.text:
Commonly known as the blue roundhead, this is an inedible species of agaric #fungus. This #mushroom is a common species that can be found growing as a saprophyte in meadows, roadsides, hedgerows, gardens, and woodchip mulch throughout North America and Europe. 

#FungusFriday 🍄 📸 by TorriPhoto/Getty

The Tyrannosaurus rex lived at the very end of the Late Cretaceous, which was about 90 to 66 million years ago. 🦖

Paleontologists have found the majority of T. Rex fossils in western North America in states such as Montana and South Dakota. T. rex fossils have also been found in Alberta, Canada.

Stentors are resilient micro animals. Check this stentor coeruleus out for example. It may have been destroyed when filamentous algae were added to the slide, but that doesn’t mean it’s waving the white flag.

Do you see this big blue chunk attached to the stentor? This chunk is going to regenerate into a whole new healthy stentor.
